<paragraph id="102F1707FF96FFC6E7B0AE5A84FBFCF0" blockId="8.[151,1436,537,994]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<taxonomicName id="D7906C84FF96FFC6E7B0AE5A875FFD90" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,270,537,562]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E7B0AE5A875FFD90" box="[151,270,537,562]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrow range in the south-west corner of Anatolia and its range is geographically very heterogeneous. Some other lineages restricted to the same area, exhibit interesting patterns of diversity and the Demre district seems to be special (
<bibRefCitation id="74016AF6FF96FFC6E502AE2184B4FDD8" box="[549,741,609,634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref17258" refString="Veith, M. E., Oz, M., Kiefer, A., Baran, I., Polymeni, R. M. &amp; Steinfartz, S. (2008) Cracking the nut: geographical adjacency of sister taxa supports vicariance in a polytomic salamander clade in the absence of node support. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 47, 916 - 931. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2007.11.017" type="journal article">
Veith 
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E54EAE2284C8FDD8" box="[617,665,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="74016AF6FF96FFC6E5D7AE22859CFDD8" box="[752,973,609,634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref15450" refString="Boztepe, Z., Kaya, S. &amp; Ciplak, B. (2013) Integrated systematics of the Poecilimon luschani species group (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae): radiation as a chain of populations in a small heterogeneous area. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169, 43 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12058" type="journal article">
Boztepe 
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E474AE2285DAFDD8" box="[851,907,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="74016AF6FF96FFC6E4FEAE2282C6FDD8" box="[985,1175,609,634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref16754" refString="Kaya, S., Boztepe, Z. &amp; Ciplak, B. (2015) Phylogeography of the Poecilimon luschani species group (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae): a radiation strictly correlated with climatic transitions in the Pleistocene. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 173 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12202" type="journal article">
Kaya 
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E33CAE228205FDD8" box="[1051,1108,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). This speciality is also observed for 
<taxonomicName id="D7906C84FF96FFC6E609AEC687CEFD3C" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[302,415,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E609AEC687CEFD3C" box="[302,415,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and the extensive material showed that the Kemer-Demre population of 
<taxonomicName id="D7906C84FF96FFC6E20CAEC683CDFD3C" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[1323,1436,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E20CAEC683CDFD3C" box="[1323,1436,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs morphologically from that in the remaining western part of the range. We decided to indicate this diversity to the taxonomy of species by defining the Demre population as a separate taxon. As reproductive isolation between these forms needs further testing we defined the latter population as a separate subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="D7906C84FF96FFC6E20EAEB2868BFC8C" authority="Kaya &amp; Chobanov &amp; Heller &amp; Yahyaoğlu &amp; Uluar &amp; Çiplak, 2018" authorityName="Kaya &amp; Chobanov &amp; Heller &amp; Yahyaoğlu &amp; Uluar &amp; Çiplak" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="inflatus" status="subsp. n." subSpecies="lyciae">
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E20EAEB2868BFC8C" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus lyciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39D7766EFF96FFC6E7C1AF558705FC8C" box="[230,340,789,814]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" rank="subSpecies">
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E7C1AF558705FC8C" bold="true" box="[230,340,789,814]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">subsp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Description of 
<taxonomicName id="D7906C84FF96FFC6E535AF5684D7FC8C" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[530,646,789,814]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis id="22E4CB15FF96FFC6E535AF5684D7FC8C" box="[530,646,789,814]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was supplemented by 
<bibRefCitation id="74016AF6FF96FFC6E4BEAF558267FC8C" box="[921,1078,789,814]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref15951" refString="Heller, K. G. (2004) Poecilimon martinae n. sp. and P. inflatus Brunner von Wattenywyl, 1891 (Orthoptera, Tettigonioidea, Phaneropteridae), two bush-cricket species endemic to southwest Anatolia: morphology, bioacoustics and systematics. Articulata, 19, 1 - 17." type="journal article">Heller (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and is also valid for the new subspecies except for the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="102F1707FF96FFC6E7E0AF1D8333FC40" blockId="8.[151,1436,537,994]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<materialsCitation id="A0F81D5AFF96FFC6E7E0AF1D8333FC40" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1913893128" country="Turkey" location="Aydin Province" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Aydin Province">
<bibRefCitation id="74016AF6FF96FFC6E7E0AF1D8729FCD4" box="[199,376,861,886]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref16622" refString="Karabag, T. (1958) Orthoptera Fauna of Turkey (Turkiye'nin Orthoptera faunasi) Ankara Universitesi Fen Fakultesi Yayinlari, Ankara-Turkey, 98 pp." type="book">Karabağ (1958)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from Bölüntü (
<collectingRegion id="D254D9E5FF96FFC6E43DAF1D859AFCD4" box="[794,971,861,886]" country="Turkey" name="Aydin" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Aydın Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="68875797FF96FFC6E4D4AF1D8214FCD4" box="[1011,1093,861,886]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Turkey</collectingCountry>
) on the basis of one male and one female. Although field studies by one of the authors (SK) has been done in this locality on the same date as reported no sample was found. This locality is far from the presently confirmed range of the species and needs confirmation. On the other hand it is difficult to assign it to any subspecies without examining the specimens.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
